{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To train NeST-VNN, we leveraged drug response data for 1,244 genomically characterized tumor cell lines 23, obtained by harmonizing the Cancer Therapeutics Response Portal (CTRP) 24, 25 and Genomics of Drug Sensitivity in Cancer (GDSC) 26, 27 databases (Methods).",
    "These data included the response to the CDK4/6i palbociclib, which had been well characterized in 947 cell lines.",
    "For comparative benchmarking, we also examined 50 non-CDK-related drugs investigated in at least 200 cell lines, for which the cellular responses displayed sufficient variability, with many examples of sensitivity and resistance (Methods).",
    "We constructed NeST-VNN drug response models for palbociclib and separately for each of the 50 benchmark drugs, using standard neural network learning procedures based on backpropagation (Methods).",
    "Each model was trained to use the gene alteration profile of a cell line to predict the corresponding area under the dose-response curve (AUC)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To train NeST-VNN, we leveraged drug response data for 1,244 genomically characterized tumor cell lines 23, obtained by harmonizing the Cancer Therapeutics Response Portal (CTRP) 24, 25 and Genomics of Drug Sensitivity in Cancer (GDSC) 26, 27 databases (Methods)."
  ]
}